TITLE: Resizing Canvas in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This function resizes the canvas element based on the client width and height, scaled by the pixel ratio. It returns true if the canvas was resized, and false otherwise.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ui-layouts/cursify/blob/main/content/components/fluid-cursor.mdx#_snippet_34

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
function resizeCanvas() {
  let width = scaleByPixelRatio(canvas.clientWidth);
  let height = scaleByPixelRatio(canvas.clientHeight);
  if (canvas.width != width || canvas.height != height) {
    canvas.width = width;
    canvas.height = height;
    return true;
  }
  return false;
}
```

