TITLE: Generate Hash Code for String
DESCRIPTION: This function, `hashCode`, generates a hash code for a given string. It iterates through the string, applying a bitwise operation to calculate the hash. It returns 0 if the string is empty. The bitwise operations and shifting are for performance and distribution of the hash value.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ui-layouts/cursify/blob/main/content/components/fluid-cursor.mdx#_snippet_60

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
function hashCode(s) {
  if (s.length == 0) return 0;
  let hash = 0;
  for (let i = 0; i < s.length; i++) {
    hash = (hash << 5) - hash + s.charCodeAt(i);
    hash |= 0; // Convert to 32bit integer
  }
  return hash;
}
```

