TITLE: Blur Vertex Shader
DESCRIPTION: This GLSL vertex shader calculates texture coordinates for a blur effect. It is similar to the base vertex shader but includes an offset for the blurred samples.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ui-layouts/cursify/blob/main/content/components/fluid-cursor.mdx#_snippet_11

LANGUAGE: GLSL
CODE:
```
       precision highp float;

       attribute vec2 aPosition;
       varying vec2 vUv;
       varying vec2 vL;
       varying vec2 vR;
       uniform vec2 texelSize;

       void main () {
           vUv = aPosition * 0.5 + 0.5;
           float offset = 1.33333333;
           vL = vUv - texelSize * offset;
           vR = vUv + texelSize * offset;
           gl_Position = vec4(aPosition, 0.0, 1.0);
       }

```

