TITLE: Fragment Shader: Curl Calculation (GLSL)
DESCRIPTION: This GLSL fragment shader calculates the curl (vorticity) of a velocity field. It samples the velocity texture at the current fragment and its neighboring fragments (left, right, top, bottom) to compute the curl using a finite difference approximation.  The result is then halved before being assigned to the output color's x component.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ui-layouts/cursify/blob/main/content/components/fluid-cursor.mdx#_snippet_21

LANGUAGE: GLSL
CODE:
```
precision mediump float;
precision mediump sampler2D;

varying highp vec2 vUv;
varying highp vec2 vL;
varying highp vec2 vR;
varying highp vec2 vT;
varying highp vec2 vB;
uniform sampler2D uVelocity;

void main () {
    float L = texture2D(uVelocity, vL).y;
    float R = texture2D(uVelocity, vR).y;
    float T = texture2D(uVelocity, vT).x;
    float B = texture2D(uVelocity, vB).x;
    float vorticity = R - L - T + B;
gl_FragColor = vec4(0.5 * vorticity, 0.0, 0.0, 1.0);
}

```

